channel.title: Help needed! asap!
channel.description:
Hello, i am not a complete new person to servers i have a server and everything, i mean like I know most of the basics and stuff(except for majority of important ones) and i really need help. Here are the questions and things i need help with. (by the way this is a 317 server.)
1. How can i get my server online without port-forwarding? :confused:
2. How can i make it so that a God Sword is the correct two-handed wield, instead of on right shoulder?
3. How do i add shops?
4. How can i add custom items, and make them.
5. How can i edit the rules?
6. How can i change what it says in chat box when you log in?
7. How can i add items to the server, such as Dragon Claws, with correct emote, wield, and special? (i mean like if an item is either nulled or just not added at all.)
8. Any suggestions for a good [[317 NOT DELTA!]] server and source to use? like any recommendations?
9. How do i add mini-games or things like god wars dungeon, pest control, and barrows?
...and so that is all i can think of needing help with at the moment. If i think of some else i will add it, and please help and respond asap, because i can't wait! lol, and yes it is long :eek: :eek: :eek:

item.title: Help needed! asap!
item.dc:creator: @usman555 usman555
item.description:
@usman555 wrote:

We don’t spoonfeed. Do these things yourself and when you hit an error or don’t understand something, post it here.
Asking how to make an entire minigame is saying “I can’t go to the tutorials section, so I’ll just wait for someone to spoonfeed me all the way.”

  1. uTorrent. Follow guides in the tutorial section

  2. Put the item ID in the two_handed array in client.java

  3. Search Button / Youtube / Tutorials Section

  4. http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,363483.0.html

  5. We don’t spoonfeed this is easy enough. If you can’t find out, I’m sure theres a beginners tutorial in the tutorial section

  6. This is the exact same as answer 5

  7. If your talking about adding models, then go here http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,363483.0.html

  8. You should test out sources ON YOUR OWN. What do you mean by “best”? You didn’t even say “best pk source” or “best skilling source”. Even if you did, you need to test them out yourself.

  9. We don’t spoonfeed, go to the tutorials section
